{"word":"G447 - ἀνίημι - aníēmi - an-ee'-ay-mee - Forbear","slug":"G447","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀνίημι</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>aníēmi"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>an-ee'-ay-mee"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Forbear"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B1;&#x0313;&#x03BD;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03B7;&#x03BC;&#x03B9; - anie&#x0304;mi</b> - <i>an-ee'-ay-mee</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G303\">G303</a> and <b>&#x03B9;&#x0314;&#x0301;&#x03B7;&#x03BC;&#x03B9;</b> <b>hie&#x0304;mi</b> (to <i>send</i>); to <i>let up</i>, that is, (literally) <i>slacken</i>, or (figuratively) <i>desert</i>, <i>desist</i> from: - forbear, leave, loose."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G425\">G425</a>"}]}